// gravity_lab — dedicated gravity test room (Jon redirect 2026-06-03).
//
// Jon: "We can't have the gravity columns in the main sandbox room, we have to
// create a separate gravity room for testing." This is that room. The gravity
// COLUMNS themselves are debug-spawned in Rust (portal::spawn_debug_gravity_zone_once)
// gated to this room id, positioned relative to PlayerStart; the global
// gravity-flip switch stays in the main sandbox room.
//
// Demo: a puppy slug stands where the up-gravity column spawns, so it falls UP
// and crawls along the ceiling — proving gravity is local in space (an actor in
// the column feels the column even though the global ambient is down).
//
// Reached from central_hub_main via the lab-door row (px [917, 880], a free slot
// reported by `door free-spots central_hub_main`).
//
// Layout (1024×640):
//
//   +--------------------------------------------------+  ceiling
//   |                                                  |
//   |            [up-gravity column ~px 336..616]      |
//   |   ____             (puppy slug falls up)         |
//   |  start            [mid platform]                 |
//   |  [P]    [slug]                                   |
//   +--------------------------------------------------+  floor
//
